caption: I eat in this spot a lot since I work close by. I got to say the customer service is always excellent and they keep the place clean constantly. Pricing is affordable and they serve large portions.
Great food.  Great service!!

This was a good Greek joint. The hot dogs were tasty and their wraps did the trick. However, I feel that the food didn't reach it's potential to truly be great. I wish they had more personal french fries. There are other joints with the same price for fries and more for the amount.
The place offers an awesome variety of fresh food. I loved eating here. Employees are always helpful, rates are fair and the spot is always well organised.

This spot is the one I always prefer. I go to many restaurants but here I go the most. The stuff is very affectionate and the cuisine they cook is so flavorful. I am always happy to have a good dinner in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.

This spot is worth visiting. They serve large portions for convenient rates. Consistently well organized and with good atmosphere. Will come visit again.

You can tell the meat and toppings were fresh.  Great service, as well.  One of the best gyros I have had in the US. I, also, loved the crinkle fries too.  If you love a ‘softer’ (my personal preference) french fry then these are top notch.

I’m sorry but the people giving the 4 stars have clearly never tasted authentic Greek Food. Tziki has to be made with yogurt & cucumber & garlic the water downed version this place made is horrible. The chicken souvlaki was horrible and they clearly cannot cook fresh Greek Food. Don’t waste your money. I cried over the twenty dollars for food I could not even eat!!! 😡

Cheap and good

Order the usual lamb yeero. Before I had time to seat and wait for my order food was already coming out. How that quick!??? The bread was soggy and burning hot right out of the microwave and lamb already cook and soaked from seating on its own grease. I thought the food in this place is made as you order not precooked and microwaved ready to go! For that I would've gone to a fast food place.

Best Greek food in the area and they sell beer. The owner and his staff are some of the nicest people I have met. Their food is always fresh and full of flavor. They are conveniently located directly off of University Boulevard and have a large parking lot. They are one of only two beer stores in four corners
Great little counter service Greek restaurant. Food is fast, good, and cheap. Highly recommend for a summer afternoon to get a beer and a gyro.

Fabulous place for inexpensive food and beer.
Food was good, but can be made more yummy with more onions n spice. We had chic  steak n Gyro.

Had the burger with the wierdest name here. It was amazing. It's the one with a lamb patty and a beef patty. Try it. You may want to go light on the onions.  A little too much. Otherwise,  a great place for a quick lunch.

A little restaurant with big time flavor. Authentic greek food, prepared and brought to your table by a friendly employee. The seating area is small but has a large flat screen TV, and there are beer specials on Sundays during football games. Convenient parking situated just two turns of University Boulevard. Beer is sold by the bottle and in six packs, and whole bottles of wine are available for purchase. Must have gyro and baklava!!!
Great place for a quick bite or drink!
I just love the mom and pop places !!! This is what Jerrys was like before it became plastic franchise food
Look up local Greek style restaurant small good food good value they focus on beer and wine sales but if you're looking for a little taste of Greek its o.k.
They left multiple things off of our order, food arrived cold. Tzatziki sauce is very watery. Will not be ordering again

I was expecting more from this establishment.  I ordered the typical gyro.  It was quite dry and lackluster.  It may have been a fluke; I'll have to give them another chance.  The gyro from arby's beat this "authentic" version easily.  Maybe that it's more telling of my tastes than the quality of their food.  Parking is nearly non-existent, so keep that in mind.
Food was good, but a bit bland.  Friendly staff.

Don't be fooled by appearance. This place might be small and not look like much but the food is amazing and they treat you like they've known you for years. My only complaint is that I don't live close enough to eat there every day. I will definitely keep this on my list of places to eat when I go back to Baltimore.

I was a tad disappointed as this was one of my favorite spots for gyros. Although service was quick and food was hot,both gyros were missing my favorite toppings. Something about the fresh cucumbers and feta,with the onions, tomatoes,and cucumber sauce brings it together. The cucumbers and feta weren't present and I wanted more cucumber sauce because hey that's what really brings it out. The calamari was another flop,if you like frozen calamari go for it,but as a true calamari fan I was not a happy camper.

Lady at the counter is super friendly. Food here is fast, tasty, and cheap. If you're visiting the parking is good, not many seats for dining in,  but there is also outdoor seating which is very nice this time of year!

I really enjoy their lamb gyro, I can't say anything about any other item since that is basically all I get, but I appreciate how they put, what seems like to me extra lamb and lots of onions, I like their fries and the fact that they actually put some flavor directly into their fries!
